{"lemma":"هَشٌّ","slug":"هَشٌّ","root":"ه.ش.ش","root_slug":"ه-ش-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ش-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41193"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to beat down (leaves, branches)","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ هِيَ عَصَايَ أَتَوَكَّأُ عَلَيْهَا وَأَهُشُّ بِهَا عَلَىٰ غَنَمِي وَلِيَ فِيهَا مَآرِبُ أُخْرَىٰ","english":"He said, \"It is my stick. I lean on it, I beat down with it for my sheep, and I have many other uses of it."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smile; to make a friendly expression","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"عندما وجدته عرّفته بنفسي، فهشّ في وجهي وقال لي إنّه في خدمتي.","english":"When I found him, I made my presence known to him, whereupon he behaved politely towards me and told me he would be in my service."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fragile, crisp"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cordial, welcoming"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Possibly onomatopoeic."},"ipa":["/haʃ.ʃa/","/haʃʃ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41193","headword_ar":"هَشٌّ","root":"h$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A thing, (S, Msb,) or anything, (JK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, yielding, flaccid, flabby, lax, slack, uncompact, crummy, fragile, frangible, brittle, friable, easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * S, * A, * Msb, K, * TA;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rixowN lay~inN","text_ar":"رِخْوٌ لَيِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$iy$N","text_ar":"هَشِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozN ha$~N","text_ar":"خُبْزٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$aA$N","text_ar":"هَشَاشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bread that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy to break."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozapN ha$~apN","text_ar":"خُبْزَةٌ هَشَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lump of dough, baked in a fire in the ground, that is dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"asserted by IKtt to have two contr. significations. (TA.) [But to this assertion it may be replied, that dry bread is easy to break.] And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^utoruj~apN ha$~apN","text_ar":"اُتْرُجَّةٌ هَشَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A citron easy to break:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwdN ha$~N","text_ar":"عُودٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stick, that is easily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly broken."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa ha$~N","text_ar":"هُوَ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosiri","text_ar":"المَكْسِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosari","text_ar":"المَكْسَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [but this is contr. to all the other authorities that I know,]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almukas~ari","text_ar":"المُكَسَّرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compliant, when asked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is of easy nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to what is sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demanded, of him, of things needed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) said in praise of a man (S, TA) when it means [lit.] that he is not one whose wood gives only a sound when one endeavours to produce fire from it; but said in dispraise of a man when it means [lit.] that he is one whose wood is weak. (TA.) [And in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$iy$N","text_ar":"هَشِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA$~N","text_ar":"هَاشٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) signify (tropical:)  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who rejoices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is glad, when asked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa haA$N","text_ar":"هُوَ هَاشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda Als~uw^aAli","text_ar":"عِنْدَ السُّوَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ha$iy$N","text_ar":"هَشِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who rejoices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is glad, at being asked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N A_ilaY A_ixowaAnihi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ اـِلَى اـِخْوَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA$~N","text_ar":"هَاشٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly, in his behaviour towards his brethren."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N ba$~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ بَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful in countenance; pleasant"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b$","text_ar":"بش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA bihi ha$~N ba$~N","text_ar":"اَنَا بِهِ هَشٌّ بَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am cheerful, brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly, in behaviour towards him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joyful; happy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN ha$~N fuw^aAduhu","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ هَشٌّ فُوَادُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prompt, to do good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fara$N ha$~u","text_ar":"فَرَشٌ هَشُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEinaAni","text_ar":"العِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that is brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of rein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN ha$~N","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ هَشٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse that sweats much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, IF, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaluwdN","text_ar":"صَلُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Slwd","text_ar":"صلود"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","JK","K","A","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}